				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: my gear, any idea on what to upgrade?<a name="74086"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 7 05 3:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>JF increases the effective level of a song such that it will have the same effect as a song sung at a higher level.  This means added regen / stats / debuff / dot / mana etc over and above what you would normally obtain for a given level.
<br />

<br />
I personally did not experience anything noticeable happening to resists when I moved from JF0 to JF3.  General consensus is that it does not change resist rates, though the evidence either way appears anecdotal.  Read the following thread on TCH : <a target="_new" href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallfrm8.showMessage?topicID=94.topic">http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallfrm8.showMessage?topicID=94.topic</a>
<br />

<br />
______
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Cha and Agi are by far the hardest stats to bring up. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
And AGI is as good as useless.  Ignore it totally when choosing items. To quote the tester Coprolith, <i>&quot;As it is, a 3% increase in avoidance for a 100 AGI increase is a joke anyway, SOE might as well remove the stat completely and reduce the CPU load of having to calculate its effect.&quot;</i>.  (for full thread see : <a target="_new" href="http://www.beastlords.org/forums/index.php?topic=1944.0">http://www.beastlords.org/forums/index.php?topic=1944.0</a>)
<br />

<br />
I'm inclined to agree with him, as SW parses show (<a target="_new" href="http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=145&amp;page=2&amp;pp=15">http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=145&amp;page=2&amp;pp=15</a>) this 3pc avoidance to be comparable to the mitigation effect of 60 worn ac or so for a typical xp mob (which was in PoF).
<br />

<br />
I suggested INT and mana as being important not for charm solo purposes (FT is more important for this as you require sustained mana), but to increase survivability and pulling capabilities.  More mana = more fades in a row, and more consecutive fades means you have a greater ability to <i>break</i> tough camps or get into 'impossible' places.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
