				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: my gear, any idea on what to upgrade?<a name="74196"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 05 2:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Manizeh :
<br />

<br />
I wasnt knocking ac at all <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  I'm actually an ac freak, and would take 10 ac over 40 hp anyday -- but thats personal opinion I guess.  
<br />

<br />
Note though that your displayed ac is a composite number of mitigation (ie worn) ac and avoidance (ie defense skill and AGI) ac.   They have different effects.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and mitigation does NOT depend on class.  A wizzy with, say, 1500 ac will mitigate equally as well as a knight with 1500ac.  The difference in tanking abilities is only due to the lower avoidance caps (being defense / dodge / block / parry / riposte); there is a parse in the EQClerics forum library, and much discussion, concerning this.   This is why the not infrequent grumbles by bards about not having proper plate mitigation are so much rubbish.  What we really mean to ask for is an increase in avoidance skill caps.
<br />

<br />
You are right to state that ac softens damage spikes.  Still trying to persuade my guild's raid leader that a bard should be with MA for added ac, but he doesnt believe ac does much.  Cant wait for server merge and my free /movelog ......</span></td>
