				<td colspan="2"><span>For whoever was saying charisma is unnecessary &lt;Egfrith?&gt;
<br />

<br />
Charisma, in addition to affecting resist rates and break rate on charm, also affects -for bards anyhow- missed notes rates. Currently, I am ~270-ish on unbuffed charisma, and I do notice a marked difference when I get shaman charisma buff on me &lt;puts me at 329, one point from max&gt; in the number of missed notes I get. Up till /melody, I didn't care at all. But now.... its a different story. Dexterity... well its always maxed, so not sure on the affect of Dex on missed notes, I think it is mostly only desired for consideration in relation to proccing weapons.
<br />

<br />
Agi and Cha ARE the hardest stats to max though.</span></td>
