				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I don't care how many times it gets resisted so long as it's not a critical resist. And a larger debuff = less resists. </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
Jam Fest has no effect in debuffing resists, unless you are using a dot, which makes the mob unmazzable. HoS is a set amount of debuff that does not scale up with level, hence the debuffed amount is a fix number that only depends on your percussion mod, not level.
<br />

<br />
For Mean_Raid_Mob_01 sometimes I use the Ancient dot on top of HoS for a total debuff of (15 + 9 + extra JF3 dot debuff) * (1 + Percussion Instrument mod + IM4)
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Hmmm... I didn&#180;t know a wizzard with the same AC mitigates just as a Warrior would do. It seems wrong though. There should be some class innate skill built in IMO.</span></td>
